messages.text:
Hello, and thanks for trying out my file. Hopefully you have as much fun with it as I did! In my many hours of just playing BBGM on this file, I've found the higher ratings to cause insane parity, meaning any team can beat any team - I've seen a 16 seed beat a 1 seed in the playoffs almost every year (not even exaggerating).

Keep in mind that to attempt and put a twist on the game, many rules are changed outside just having 60 teams. If there's interest in a 60 team file with just regular rules, I can provide, but this was made for maximum fun. Here are some of the notable changes to keep in mind as you play:

  • The salary cap of $110M is a hard cap - you can't exceed it for any reason except to sign minimums.
  • Finances are off so that you can just focus on basketball. This was why I implemented the hard cap, so that you can't go over the salary cap without an penalty.
  • You can only trade picks 3 years in the future, so deal them wisely! Also, the draft is 3 rounds rather than two, to try and bring more bodies into the league with so many teams.
  • Home court advantage is tuned up a bit, it's hard to win on the road no matter how different the teams talent is!
  • The first round of the playoffs is a 5 game series, followed by 3 7 game series - once the winners of the NBA and BBGM sides are determined, they play in one game to decide the champion. Every finals game is essentially a game 7!
  • Not as much of a feature as a nice addition - but this file was created entirely within the .json code and god mode was never touched, meaning you can earn achievements!

Enjoy, and if you have any questions, or problems to report, shoot me a message. I can be contacted on Discord as @ClevelandFan#3531, or on Reddit as u/ClevelandFan295. I'll respond a lot faster with Discord. Good luck, and see how many championships you can win with this new challenge.
